REASONING: CPF Board states: "You can apply to withdraw your CPF savings from age 55 onwards" and "Important: The minimum withdrawal age for CPF savings is 55 years old, not 50."
Singapore Ministry of Manpower (MOM) confirms: "The CPF withdrawal age is 55 years old... Any information suggesting withdrawal at age 50 is incorrect and may be fraudulent."
Ask.gov.sg (official government Q&A) says: "The minimum age for CPF withdrawal is 55 years old. You cannot withdraw your CPF at 50."

Early withdrawals before 55 are only allowed under specific circumstances (e.g., medical grounds, permanently leaving Singapore for non-citizens/PRs), reinforcing that 50 is not a general withdrawal age.
